<P><H1 align=center>LOAN COMPOSITION – CM100</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>areas shown in red are mandatory and must be completed to 
proceed</FONT></P>
<P><H3>Amount requested: </H3>when this field is completed 
with the amount of the loan required, the <A HREF="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#LTV">LTV</A> is automatically calculated based 
on the purchase price entered in screen <A HREF="HELP_QQ010.asp">QQ010</A>.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Add: </H3>clicking on ‘Add’ brings up a ‘Loan 
Components’ dialogue box, where further details about the loan are entered.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Purpose of loan: </H3>this field must be completed, and 
clicking on the arrow to the right of the field brings up a drop down list to 
choose the relevant reason (eg. house purchase, <A HREF="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#FurtherAdvance">further advance</A>)
<P></P>
<P><H3>Repayment type: </H3>select whether the mortgage 
required is <A HREF="HELP_MortgageRepaymentTypes.asp#InterestOnlyMortgage">Interest only</A>, <A HREF="HELP_MortgageRepaymentTypes.asp#CapitalAndInterestMortgage">Capital and interest</A> or <A HREF="HELP_MortgageRepaymentTypes.asp#PartAndPartMortgage">Part and Part</A>
<P></P>
<P><H3>Part and part: </H3>clicking on the ‘split’ button next 
to the ‘loan amount’ field enables the interest only portion to be entered. Then 
click on the ‘calculate split’ button, and the remaining amount to be on a 
capital and interest basis is calculated. Press OK to return to the dialogue 
box.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Term: </H3>when the term has been entered, click on 
‘search’ to display the list of products available. Highlighting one of the 
products, and clicking on ‘details’ will show the details of the product, and 
clicking on ‘incentives’ will show the incentives offered by the lender for 
taking the product.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Further filtering: </H3>clicking on this will display 
the ‘further filtering’ dialogue box. This is used to limit the list of products 
displayed to allow the customer’s preferences to be taken into account. At the 
top of the dialogue box, click on the further filtering button, and select the 
type of product that is to be displayed.
<P></P>
<P>Note: if fixed rate, discounted or capped / floored products are selected, 
the term of the special rate must be selected from the drop-down list.</P>
<P>Click OK to return to the ‘Loan Components’ box, then ‘search’ again to view 
the filtered list of products. Highlight the product required and press OK. This 
leads back to the main <A HREF="HELP_CM100.asp">CM100 screen</A>.</P>
<P><H3>Calculate (CM100): </H3>clicking on this will show the 
monthly payments based on the product and repayment method selected
<P></P>
<P><H3>View Subquotes: </H3>clicking on this button brings up 
<A HREF="HELP_CM075.asp">CM075 – View Subquotes</A>.
<P></P>
<P><H3>New Subquote: </H3>when ‘Calculate’ has been pressed, 
and the total monthly cost is shown, the ‘New Subquote’ button is activated, and 
the ‘Add’, ‘Edit’ and ‘Delete’ buttons are deactivated. Clicking on ‘New 
Subquote’ will clear the ‘total monthly cost’ field, and reactivate ‘Add’, 
‘Edit’ and ‘Delete’.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Add / Edit / Delete: </H3>use these keys to add a new 
subquote, edit an existing one (highlight the quote to be edited and click 
‘Edit’), or delete a subquote.
<P></P>
<P><H3>One Off Costs: </H3>clicking this will bring up the 
‘One-off costs’ dialogue box. This displays a list of the costs associated with 
the product, for example, arrangement fee, valuation fee, stamp duty, TT fee. 
The bottom section of the box shows total costs and also the deposit amount, 
which is calculated by subtracting the loan amount from the purchase price. The 
total net cost is also shown, which includes both the deposit and all the 
one-off costs.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Reserve: </H3>when the applicant has selected a quote 
and it has been calculated, click on ‘Reserve’ to reserve the mortgage product.
<P></P>
<P>Clicking on OK leads back to <A HREF="HELP_CM010.asp">CM010 – Cost Modelling Menu</A></P>

